items.title: MLB celebrates Hispanic Heritage Month
items.summary: Major League Baseball announced Wednesday that it will continue to celebrate Hispanic Heritage Month with a series of initiatives and events showcasing the contributions of Hispanic and Latino players.
items.content: Major League Baseball announced Wednesday that it will continue to celebrate Hispanic Heritage Month with a series of initiatives and events showcasing the contributions of Hispanic and Latino players.

items.title: Rays to host Sox at the Trop this weekend
items.summary: The Rays are heading home to Tropicana Field to play the division-rival Red Sox after their series against the Yankees was relocated because of Hurricane Irma, which swept through the entire state of Florida earlier this week.
items.content: The Rays are heading home to Tropicana Field to play the division-rival Red Sox after their series against the Yankees was relocated because of Hurricane Irma, which swept through the entire state of Florida earlier this week.

items.title: A's select site, reveal plans for new ballpark
items.summary: The A's have handpicked land near Oakland's Laney College as the site they'd like to build a privately financed new stadium, with hopes of breaking ground in 2021 and opening two years later.
items.content: The A's have handpicked land near Oakland's Laney College as the site they'd like to build a privately financed new stadium, with hopes of breaking ground in 2021 and opening two years later.
